    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="The new PlayStation 5 slim and standard PlayStation 5 standing vertically side by side on a table." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/86-WrbbFmeNTswwljr_EiMMyxZk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73604709/110923_new_Playstation_5_Slim_ADiBenedetto_0010.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Antonio G. Di Benedetto / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="a7xvFD"&gt;Get ready to see more PlayStation games. Sony is hosting a State of Play presentation tomorrow, September 24th, and &lt;a href="https://blog.playstation.com/2024/09/23/state-of-play-returns-tomorrow/"&gt;the company says&lt;/a&gt; it will feature news and updates on “more than 20 upcoming PS5 and PS VR2 games from studios around the world.” Sony says the State of Play will be more than 30 minutes long, and you’ll be able to watch it at 6PM ET / 3PM PT on YouTube and Twitch. &lt;/p&gt;
