    <title>Google is bringing its smart home panel to all Google TV devices</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="The new smart home panel on the Google TV Streamer is coming to all Google TV devices." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tLFt1vzGKtxubh__0JrWhja1Bn0=/600x0:3840x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73604683/Smart_Home_Control_Panel_Google_TV_Streamer.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: Google&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="dK8v6d"&gt;Google announced today that it’s extending all the software features of its &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/23/24250684/google-tv-streamer-4k-review-smart-home-hub"&gt;new Google TV Streamer&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href="https://blog.google/products/google-tv/google-tv-home-ai-sports-features/"&gt;every Google TV device&lt;/a&gt;. This includes its smart home control panel, a new sports page, and new Gemini-powered features. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="7L3Pbf"&gt;According to Google, the updates will come to all devices, including Google TVs, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/21495609/google-chromecast-2020-review-streaming-remote-control"&gt;Chromecasts with Google TV&lt;/a&gt;, and third-party Google TV streamers (like the &lt;a href="https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2Fonn-Google-TV-4K-Pro-Streaming-Device-New-2024-4K-UHD-resolution-Dolby-Vision-Dolby-ATMOS-Hands-Free-Voice-Control-Smart-Hub%2F5193222892%3Fwmlspartner%3Dwlpa%26selectedSellerId%3D0%26wl13%3D2348%26gclsrc%3Daw.ds%26adid%3D222222222775193222892_117755028669_12420145346%26wl0%3D%26wl1%3Dg%26wl2%3Dc%26wl3%3D501107745824%26wl4%3Dpla-394283752452%26wl5%3D9189439%26wl6%3D%26wl7%3D%26wl8%3D%26wl9%3Dpla%26wl10%3D8175035%26wl11%3Dlocal%26wl12%3D5193222892%26veh%3Dsem_LIA%26gclsrc%3Daw.ds%26gad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQjwo8S3BhDeARIsAFRmkOOdoNoPHjJfY5LL4pWpI4UpEZIbB5f02qLDCjwLw6tU9Q1x-caby1QaAkF1EALw_wcB&amp;amp;sharedid=theverge.com" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Onn available at Walmart&lt;/a&gt;), in the coming weeks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="JcHsGp"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Google TV Streamer review: smarter than your average set-top box ","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/23/24250684/google-tv-streamer-4k-review-smart-home-hub"},{"title":"Google Chromecast (2020) review: reinvented — and now with a remote ","url":"https://www.theverge.com/21495609/google-chromecast-2020-review-streaming-remote-control"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="OpJjII"&gt;The biggest upgrade for smart home users is the new Home panel. This smart home control panel is accessed via a tile in the quick settings panel and lets you control devices connected to Google Home. You can do things like turn lights on or off or dim / brighten, trigger a Movie Time automation, and adjust your...&lt;/p&gt;
